{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I'm going to discuss with you three of my inventions"},{"time":5000,"text":"that can have an effect on 10 to a 100 million people,"},{"time":10000,"text":"which we will hope to see happen."},{"time":13000,"text":"We discussed, in the prior film, some of the old things that we did,"},{"time":17000,"text":"like stents and insulin pumps for the diabetic."},{"time":20000,"text":"And I'd like to talk very briefly about three new inventions"},{"time":25000,"text":"that will change the lives of many people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29000,"text":"At the present time, it takes an average of three hours"},{"time":32000,"text":"after the first symptoms of a heart attack are recognized by the patient,"},{"time":35000,"text":"before that patient arrives at an emergency room."},{"time":39000,"text":"And people with silent ischemia --"},{"time":41000,"text":"which, translated into English, means they don't have any symptoms --"},{"time":45000,"text":"it takes even longer for them to get to the hospital."},{"time":48000,"text":"The AMI, Acute Myocardial Infarction,"},{"time":52000,"text":"which is a doctor's big word so they can charge you more money --"},{"time":55000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":57000,"text":"-- means a heart attack. Annual incidence: 1.2 million Americans."},{"time":61000,"text":"Mortality: 300,000 people dying each year."},{"time":65000,"text":"About half of them, 600,000, have permanent damage to their heart"},{"time":71000,"text":"that will cause them to have very bad problems later on."},{"time":76000,"text":"Thus 900,000 people either have died"},{"time":79000,"text":"or have significant damage to their heart muscle."},{"time":82000,"text":"Symptoms are often denied by the patient, particularly us men,"},{"time":86000,"text":"because we are very brave. We are very brave,"},{"time":89000,"text":"and we don't want to admit that I'm having a hell of a chest pain."},{"time":93000,"text":"Then, approximately 25 percent of all patients never have any symptoms."},{"time":98000,"text":"What are we going to do about them? How can we save their lives?"},{"time":101000,"text":"It's particularly true of diabetics and elderly women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105000,"text":"Well, what is needed for the earliest possible warning of a heart attack?"},{"time":110000,"text":"A means to determine if there's a complete blockage of a coronary artery."},{"time":114000,"text":"That, ladies and gentlemen, is a heart attack."},{"time":118000,"text":"The means consist of noting something a little technical,"},{"time":122000,"text":"ST segment elevation of the electrogram --"},{"time":125000,"text":"translated into English, that means that"},{"time":128000,"text":"if there's an electrical signal in the heart, and one part of the ECG --"},{"time":134000,"text":"which we call the ST segment -- elevates,"},{"time":138000,"text":"that is a sure sign of a heart attack."},{"time":140000,"text":"And if we had a computer put into the body of a person who's at risk,"},{"time":145000,"text":"we could know, before they even have symptoms,"},{"time":148000,"text":"that they're having a heart attack, to save their life."},{"time":151000,"text":"Well, the doctor can program a level of this ST elevation voltage"},{"time":157000,"text":"that will trigger an emergency alarm,"},{"time":160000,"text":"vibration like your cell phone, but right by your clavicle bone."},{"time":165000,"text":"And when it goes beep, beep, beep, you better do something about it,"},{"time":169000,"text":"because if you want to live you have to get to some medical treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175000,"text":"So we have to try these devices out"},{"time":177000,"text":"because the FDA won't just let us use them on people"},{"time":180000,"text":"unless we try it out first,"},{"time":182000,"text":"and the best model for this happens to be pigs."},{"time":186000,"text":"And what we tried with the pig was external electrodes on the skin,"},{"time":191000,"text":"like you see in an emergency room,"},{"time":193000,"text":"and I'm going to show you why they don't work very well."},{"time":196000,"text":"And then we put a lead, which is a wire, in the right ventricle inside the heart,"},{"time":201000,"text":"which does the electrogram, which is the signal voltage from inside the heart."},{"time":205000,"text":"Well, with the pig, at the baseline,"},{"time":208000,"text":"before we blocked the pig's artery to simulate a heart attack, that was the signal."},{"time":213000,"text":"After 43 seconds, even an expert couldn't tell the difference,"},{"time":218000,"text":"and after three minutes -- well,"},{"time":220000,"text":"if you really studied it, you'd see a difference."},{"time":222000,"text":"But what happened when we looked inside the pig's heart, to the electrogram?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"There was the baseline -- first of all, a much bigger and more reliable signal."},{"time":232000,"text":"Second of all, I'll bet even you people who are untrained can see the difference,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and we see here an ST segment elevation right after this sharp line."},{"time":242000,"text":"Look at the difference there. It doesn't take much --"},{"time":246000,"text":"every layperson could see that difference,"},{"time":248000,"text":"and computers can be programmed to easily detect it."},{"time":253000,"text":"Then, look at that after three minutes."},{"time":255000,"text":"We see that the signal that's actually in the heart,"},{"time":259000,"text":"we can use it to tell people that they're having a heart attack"},{"time":263000,"text":"even before they have symptoms so we can save their life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267000,"text":"Then we tried it with my son, Dr. Tim Fischell,"},{"time":270000,"text":"we tried it on some human patients who had to have a stent put in."},{"time":274000,"text":"Well, he kept the balloon filled to block the artery,"},{"time":277000,"text":"to simulate a blockage, which is what a heart attack is."},{"time":280000,"text":"And it's not hard to see that -- the baseline"},{"time":283000,"text":"is the first picture on the upper left."},{"time":285000,"text":"Next to it, at 30 seconds, you see this rise here,"},{"time":289000,"text":"then this rise -- that's the ST elevation."},{"time":293000,"text":"And if we had a computer that could detect it,"},{"time":296000,"text":"we could tell you you're having a heart attack so early"},{"time":299000,"text":"it could save your life and prevent congestive heart failure."},{"time":304000,"text":"And then he did it again. We filled the balloon again a few minutes later"},{"time":309000,"text":"and here you see, even after 10 seconds, a great rise in this piece,"},{"time":313000,"text":"which we can have computers inside, under your chest like a pacemaker,"},{"time":318000,"text":"with a wire into your heart like a pacemaker."},{"time":321000,"text":"And computers don't go to sleep."},{"time":323000,"text":"We have a little battery and on this little battery"},{"time":327000,"text":"that computer will run for five years without needing replacement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"What does the system look like?"},{"time":333000,"text":"Well, on the left is the IMD, which is Implantable Medical Device,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and tonight in the tent you can see it -- they've exhibited it."},{"time":341000,"text":"It's about this big, the size of a pacemaker."},{"time":344000,"text":"It's implanted with very conventional techniques."},{"time":347000,"text":"And the EXD is an External Device that you can have on your night table."},{"time":351000,"text":"It'll wake you up and tell you to get your tail to the emergency room"},{"time":356000,"text":"when the thing goes off because, if you don't, you're in deep doo-doo."},{"time":360000,"text":"And then, finally, a programmer that will set the level of the stimulation,"},{"time":365000,"text":"which is the level which says you are having a heart attack."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370000,"text":"The FDA says, OK, test this final device after it's built in some animal,"},{"time":377000,"text":"which we said is a pig, so we had to get this pig to have a heart attack."},{"time":381000,"text":"And when you go to the farmyard, you can't easily get pigs to have heart attacks,"},{"time":385000,"text":"so we said, well, we're experts in stents."},{"time":388000,"text":"Tonight you'll see some of our invented stents."},{"time":390000,"text":"We said, so we'll put in a stent,"},{"time":393000,"text":"but we're not going to put in a stent that we'd put in people."},{"time":395000,"text":"We're putting in a copper stent,"},{"time":397000,"text":"and this copper stent erodes the artery and causes heart attacks."},{"time":401000,"text":"That's not very nice, but, after all, we had to find out what the answer is."},{"time":404000,"text":"So we took two copper stents and we put it in the artery of this pig,"},{"time":409000,"text":"and let me show you the result that's very gratifying"},{"time":413000,"text":"as far as people who have heart disease are concerned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"So there it was, Thursday morning we stopped the pig's medication"},{"time":422000,"text":"and there is his electrogram, the signal from inside the pig's heart"},{"time":427000,"text":"coming out by radio telemetry."},{"time":429000,"text":"Then, on Friday at 6:43, he began to get certain signs,"},{"time":434000,"text":"which later we had the pig run around --"},{"time":437000,"text":"I'm not going to go into this early stage."},{"time":440000,"text":"But look what happened at 10:06 after we removed this pig's medication"},{"time":446000,"text":"that kept him from having a heart attack."},{"time":448000,"text":"Any one of you now is an expert on ST elevation. Can you see it there?"},{"time":453000,"text":"Can you see it in the picture after the big rise of the QRS -- you see ST elevation?"},{"time":458000,"text":"This pig at 10:06 was having a heart attack."},{"time":463000,"text":"What happens after you have the heart attack, this blockage?"},{"time":467000,"text":"Your rhythm becomes irregular, and that's what happened 45 minutes later."},{"time":474000,"text":"Then, ventricular fibrillation, the heart quivers instead of beats --"},{"time":478000,"text":"this is just before death of the pig -- and then the pig died; it went flat-line."},{"time":484000,"text":"But we had a little bit over an hour where we could've saved this pig's life."},{"time":487000,"text":"Well, because of the FDA, we didn't save the pig's life,"},{"time":491000,"text":"because we need to do this type of animal research for humans."},{"time":495000,"text":"But when it comes to the sake of a human, we can save their life."},{"time":499000,"text":"We can save the lives of people who are at high risk for a heart attack."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506000,"text":"What is the response to acute myocardial infarction, a heart attack, today?"},{"time":512000,"text":"Well, you feel some chest pain or indigestion."},{"time":515000,"text":"It's not all that bad; you decide not to do anything."},{"time":518000,"text":"Several hours pass and it gets worse, and even the man won't ignore it."},{"time":523000,"text":"Finally, you go to the emergency room."},{"time":526000,"text":"You wait as burns and other critical patients are treated,"},{"time":529000,"text":"because 75 percent of the patients who go to an emergency room with chest pains"},{"time":534000,"text":"don't have AMI, so you're not taken very seriously."},{"time":538000,"text":"They finally see you. It takes more time"},{"time":540000,"text":"to get your electrocardiogram on your skin and diagnose it,"},{"time":543000,"text":"and it's hard to do because they don't have the baseline data,"},{"time":546000,"text":"which the computer we put in you gets."},{"time":550000,"text":"Finally, if you're lucky, you are treated in three or four hours after the incident,"},{"time":553000,"text":"but the heart muscle has died."},{"time":555000,"text":"And that is the typical treatment in the advanced world -- not Africa --"},{"time":560000,"text":"that's the typical treatment in the advanced world today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564000,"text":"So we developed the AngelMed Guardian System"},{"time":567000,"text":"and we have a device inside this patient, called the Implanted AngelMed Guardian."},{"time":571000,"text":"And when you have a blockage, the alarm goes off"},{"time":575000,"text":"and it sends the alarm and the electrogram to an external device,"},{"time":579000,"text":"which gets your baseline electrogram from 24 hours ago"},{"time":582000,"text":"and the one that caused the alarm, so you can take it to the emergency room"},{"time":585000,"text":"and show them, and say, take care of me right away."},{"time":589000,"text":"Then it goes to a network operations center,"},{"time":592000,"text":"where they get your data from your patient database"},{"time":594000,"text":"that's been put in at some central location, say, in the United States."},{"time":599000,"text":"Then it goes to a diagnostic center, and within one minute of your heart attack,"},{"time":603000,"text":"your signal appears on the screen of a computer"},{"time":607000,"text":"and the computer analyzes what your problem is."},{"time":610000,"text":"And the person who's there, the medical practitioner, calls you --"},{"time":614000,"text":"this is also a cell phone -- and says,"},{"time":616000,"text":"\"Mr. Smith, you're in deep doo-doo; you have a problem."},{"time":619000,"text":"We've called the ambulance. The ambulance is on the way."},{"time":623000,"text":"It'll pick you up, and then we're going to call your doctor, tell him about it."},{"time":628000,"text":"We're going to send him the signal that we have, that says you have a heart attack,"},{"time":632000,"text":"and we're going to send the signal to the hospital"},{"time":634000,"text":"and we're going to have it analyzed there,"},{"time":637000,"text":"and there you're going to be with your doctor"},{"time":639000,"text":"and you'll be taken care of so you won't die of a heart attack.\""},{"time":641000,"text":"That's the first invention that I wanted to describe."},{"time":645000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":649000,"text":"And now I want to talk about something entirely different."},{"time":652000,"text":"At first I didn't think migraine headaches were a big problem"},{"time":656000,"text":"because I'd never had a migraine headache,"},{"time":658000,"text":"but then I spoke to some people who have three or four every week of their life,"},{"time":663000,"text":"and their lives are being totally ruined by it."},{"time":666000,"text":"We have a mission statement for our company doing migraine, which is,"},{"time":670000,"text":"\"Prevent or ameliorate migraine headaches"},{"time":672000,"text":"by the application of a safe, controlled magnetic pulse"},{"time":676000,"text":"applied, as needed, by the patient.\""},{"time":679000,"text":"Now, you're probably very few physicists here."},{"time":682000,"text":"If you're a physicist you'd know there's a certain Faraday's Law,"},{"time":685000,"text":"which says if I apply a magnetic pulse on salt water --"},{"time":690000,"text":"that's your brains by the way --"},{"time":692000,"text":"it'll generate electric currents, and the electric current in the brain"},{"time":697000,"text":"can erase a migraine headache."},{"time":699000,"text":"That's what we have discovered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701000,"text":"So here's a picture of what we're doing."},{"time":704000,"text":"The patients who have a migraine preceded by an aura"},{"time":709000,"text":"have a band of excited neurons -- that's shown in red --"},{"time":713000,"text":"that moves at three to five millimeters a minute towards the mid-brain."},{"time":718000,"text":"And when it hits the mid-brain, that's when the headache begins."},{"time":723000,"text":"There's this migraine that is preceded by a visual aura,"},{"time":728000,"text":"and this visual aura, by the way -- and I'll show you a picture --"},{"time":731000,"text":"but it sort of begins with little dancing lights,"},{"time":734000,"text":"gets bigger and bigger until it fills your whole visual field."},{"time":737000,"text":"And what we tried was this; here is a device called the Cadwell Model MES10."},{"time":744000,"text":"Weighs about 70 pounds, has a wire about an inch in diameter."},{"time":748000,"text":"And here's one of the patients who has an aura"},{"time":751000,"text":"and always has a headache, bad one, after the aura. What do we do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":757000,"text":"This is what an aura looks like."},{"time":759000,"text":"It's sort of funny dancing lights, shown there on the left and right side."},{"time":763000,"text":"And that's a fully developed visual aura, as we see on top."},{"time":767000,"text":"In the middle, our experimentalist, the neurologist, who said,"},{"time":773000,"text":"\"I'm going to move this down a little and I'm going to erase half your aura.\""},{"time":776000,"text":"And, by God, the neurologist did erase it, and that's the middle picture:"},{"time":781000,"text":"half of the aura erased by a short magnetic pulse."},{"time":784000,"text":"What does that mean?"},{"time":786000,"text":"That means that the magnetic pulse is generating an electric current"},{"time":790000,"text":"that's interfering with the erroneous electrical activity in the brain."},{"time":795000,"text":"And finally he says, \"OK, now I'm going to -- \""},{"time":797000,"text":"all of the aura get erased with an appropriately placed magnetic pulse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802000,"text":"What is the result? We designed a magnetic depolarizer"},{"time":806000,"text":"that looks like this, that you could have -- a lady, in her pocket book --"},{"time":811000,"text":"and when you get an aura you can try it and see how it works."},{"time":815000,"text":"Well, the next thing they have to show is what was on ABC News,"},{"time":819000,"text":"Channel 7, last week in New York City, in the 11 o'clock news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"Anchor: For anyone who suffers from migraine headaches --"},{"time":825000,"text":"and there are 30 million Americans who do -- tonight: a possible answer."},{"time":829000,"text":"Eyewitness news reporter Stacy Sager tonight, with a small and portable machine"},{"time":833000,"text":"that literally zaps your migraines away."},{"time":837000,"text":"Christina Sidebottom: Well, my first reaction was that it was --"},{"time":839000,"text":"looked awfully gun-like, and it was very strange."},{"time":843000,"text":"Stacy Sager: But for Christina Sidebottom, almost anything was worth trying"},{"time":847000,"text":"if it could stop a migraine."},{"time":849000,"text":"It may look silly or even frightening as you walk around with it in your purse,"},{"time":855000,"text":"but researchers here in Ohio organizing clinical trials for this migraine zapper,"},{"time":860000,"text":"say it is scientifically sound --"},{"time":863000,"text":"that, in fact, when the average person gets a migraine,"},{"time":865000,"text":"it's caused by something similar to an electrical impulse."},{"time":869000,"text":"The zapper creates a magnetic field to counteract that."},{"time":873000,"text":"Yousef Mohammed: In other words, we're treating electricity with electricity,"},{"time":876000,"text":"rather than treating electricity with the chemicals that we're using nowadays."},{"time":881000,"text":"SS: But is it safe to use everyday?"},{"time":883000,"text":"Experts say the research has actually been around for more than a decade,"},{"time":887000,"text":"and more long-term studies need to be done. Christina now swears by it."},{"time":892000,"text":"CS: It's been the most wonderful thing for my migraine."},{"time":895000,"text":"SS: Researchers are hoping to present their studies to the FDA this summer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899000,"text":"Robert Fischell: And that is the invention to treat migraines."},{"time":901000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":903000,"text":"You see, the problem is, 30 million Americans have migraine headaches,"},{"time":908000,"text":"and we need a means to treat it, and I think that we now have it."},{"time":912000,"text":"And this is the first device that we did, and I'm going to talk about my second wish,"},{"time":917000,"text":"which has something to do with this."},{"time":919000,"text":"Our conclusions from our studies so far, at three research centers,"},{"time":922000,"text":"is there is a marked improvement in pain levels after using it just once."},{"time":926000,"text":"The most severe headaches responded better after we did it several times,"},{"time":931000,"text":"and the unexpected finding indicates that even established headaches,"},{"time":935000,"text":"not only those with aura, get treated and get diminished."},{"time":939000,"text":"And auras can be erased and the migraine, then, does not occur."},{"time":944000,"text":"And that is the migraine invention that we are talking about and that we are working on."},{"time":951000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":953000,"text":"The third and last invention began with an idea."},{"time":958000,"text":"Epilepsy can best be treated by responsive electrical stimulation."},{"time":963000,"text":"Now, why do we use -- add on, nearly, an epileptic focus?"},{"time":967000,"text":"Now, unfortunately, us technical people, unlike Mr. Bono,"},{"time":971000,"text":"have to get into all these technical words."},{"time":973000,"text":"Well, \"responsive electrical stimulation\" means"},{"time":978000,"text":"that we sense, at a place in your brain which is called an \"epileptic focus,\""},{"time":983000,"text":"which is where the epileptic seizure begins --"},{"time":988000,"text":"we sense there, that it's going to happen,"},{"time":991000,"text":"and then we respond by applying an electrical energy at that spot,"},{"time":996000,"text":"which erases the errant signal"},{"time":999000,"text":"so that you don't get the clinical manifestations of the migraine headache."},{"time":1004000,"text":"We use current pacemaker defibrillator technology that's used for the heart."},{"time":1009000,"text":"We thought we could adapt it for the brain."},{"time":1011000,"text":"The device could be implanted under the scalp"},{"time":1013000,"text":"to be totally hidden and avoid wire breakage,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"which occurs if you put it in the chest and you try to move your neck around."},{"time":1021000,"text":"Form a company to develop a neuro-pacemaker for epilepsy,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"as well as other diseases of the brain, because all diseases of the brain"},{"time":1030000,"text":"are a result of some electrical malfunction in it,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"that causes many, if not all, of brain disorders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039000,"text":"We formed a company called NeuroPace"},{"time":1043000,"text":"and we started work on responsive neurostimulation,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"and this is a picture of what the device looked like,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"that's placed into the cranial bone."},{"time":1052000,"text":"This is probably a better picture."},{"time":1054000,"text":"Here we have our device in which we put in a frame."},{"time":1059000,"text":"There's a cut made in the scalp; it's opened; the neurosurgeon has a template;"},{"time":1065000,"text":"he marks it around, and uses a dental burr"},{"time":1067000,"text":"to remove a piece of the cranial bone exactly the size of our device."},{"time":1072000,"text":"And tonight, you'll be able to see the device in the tent."},{"time":1075000,"text":"And then with four screws, we put in a frame,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"then we snap in the device and we run with wires --"},{"time":1082000,"text":"the one shown in green will go to the surface of the brain with electrodes,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"to the epileptic focus, the origin of the epilepsy,"},{"time":1090000,"text":"where we can sense the electrical signal"},{"time":1093000,"text":"and have computer analysis that tells us when to hit it with some electrical current"},{"time":1098000,"text":"to prevent the clinical manifestation of the seizure."},{"time":1101000,"text":"In the blue wire, we see what's called a deep brain electrode."},{"time":1104000,"text":"If that's the source of the epilepsy, we can attack that as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109000,"text":"The comprehensive solution: this is the device;"},{"time":1112000,"text":"it's about one inches by two inches and, oddly enough,"},{"time":1115000,"text":"just the thickness of most cranial bones."},{"time":1119000,"text":"The advantages of responsive neurostimulation:"},{"time":1122000,"text":"It can detect and terminate seizures before the clinical symptoms occur,"},{"time":1126000,"text":"provide stimulation only when needed,"},{"time":1129000,"text":"can be turned off if seizures disappear; it has minimal side effects --"},{"time":1134000,"text":"as a matter of fact, in all our clinical trials to date,"},{"time":1137000,"text":"we've seen no side effects in the 40 or so patients in whom it's been implanted --"},{"time":1142000,"text":"and it's invisible, cosmetically hidden,"},{"time":1145000,"text":"so, if you have epilepsy and you have the device,"},{"time":1148000,"text":"no one will know it because you can't tell that it's there."},{"time":1151000,"text":"And this shows what an electroencephalogram is,"},{"time":1155000,"text":"and on the left is the signal of a spontaneous seizure of one of the patients."},{"time":1159000,"text":"Then we stimulated, and you see how that heavy black line"},{"time":1163000,"text":"and then you see the electroencephalogram signal going to normal,"},{"time":1167000,"text":"which means they did not get the epileptic seizure."},{"time":1170000,"text":"That concludes my discussion of epilepsy,"},{"time":1175000,"text":"which is the third invention that I want to discuss here this afternoon."},{"time":1179000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1183000,"text":"I have three wishes. Well, I can't do much about Africa."},{"time":1188000,"text":"I'm a tech; I'm into medical gadgetry,"},{"time":1191000,"text":"which is mostly high-tech stuff like Mr. Bono talked about."},{"time":1195000,"text":"The first wish is to use the epilepsy responsive neurostimulator,"},{"time":1200000,"text":"called RNS, for Responsive NeuroStimulator -- that's a brilliant acronym --"},{"time":1205000,"text":"for the treatment of other brain disorders."},{"time":1207000,"text":"Well, if we're going to do it for epilepsy, why the hell not try it for something else?"},{"time":1212000,"text":"Then you saw what that device looked like,"},{"time":1215000,"text":"that the woman was using to fix her migraines?"},{"time":1217000,"text":"I tell you this: that's something which some research engineer like me would concoct,"},{"time":1222000,"text":"not a real designer of good equipment."},{"time":1224000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1226000,"text":"We want to have some people, who really know how to do this,"},{"time":1229000,"text":"perform human engineering studies to develop the optimum design"},{"time":1233000,"text":"for the portable device for treating migraine headaches."},{"time":1236000,"text":"And some of the sponsors of this TED meeting are such organizations."},{"time":1241000,"text":"Then we're going to challenge the TED attendees"},{"time":1244000,"text":"to come up with a way to improve health care in the USA,"},{"time":1248000,"text":"where we have problems that Africa doesn't have."},{"time":1251000,"text":"And by reducing malpractice litigation --"},{"time":1254000,"text":"malpractice litigation is not an African problem; it's an American problem."},{"time":1258000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1261000,"text":"So, to get quickly to my first wish --"},{"time":1264000,"text":"the brain operates by electrical signals."},{"time":1267000,"text":"If the electrical signals create a brain disorder,"},{"time":1270000,"text":"electro-stimulation can overcome that disorder by acting on the brain's neurons."},{"time":1274000,"text":"In other words, if you've screwed up electrical signals,"},{"time":1278000,"text":"maybe, by putting other electrical signals from a computer in the brain,"},{"time":1282000,"text":"we can counteract that."},{"time":1285000,"text":"A signal in the brain that triggers brain dysfunction"},{"time":1288000,"text":"might be sensed as a trigger for electro-stimulation"},{"time":1291000,"text":"like we're doing with epilepsy."},{"time":1293000,"text":"But even if there is no signal,"},{"time":1295000,"text":"electro-stimulation of an appropriate part of the brain can turn off a brain disorder."},{"time":1300000,"text":"And consider treating psychotic disorders --"},{"time":1304000,"text":"and I want this involved with the TED group --"},{"time":1307000,"text":"such as obsessive-compulsive disorder"},{"time":1309000,"text":"that, presently, is not well treated with drugs, and includes five million Americans."},{"time":1315000,"text":"And Mr. Fischer, and his group at NeuroPace, and myself believe"},{"time":1319000,"text":"that we can have a dramatic effect in improving OCD in America and in the world."},{"time":1325000,"text":"That is the first wish."},{"time":1328000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1333000,"text":"The second wish is, at the present time,"},{"time":1336000,"text":"the clinical trials of transcranial magnetic stimulators --"},{"time":1341000,"text":"that's what TMS means, device to treat migraine headaches --"},{"time":1345000,"text":"appears to be quite successful."},{"time":1347000,"text":"Well, that's the good news."},{"time":1349000,"text":"The present portable device is far from optimally designed,"},{"time":1351000,"text":"both as to human factors as appearance."},{"time":1354000,"text":"I think she said it looks like a gun. A lot of people don't like guns."},{"time":1358000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1360000,"text":"Engage a company having prior successes"},{"time":1362000,"text":"for human factors engineering and industrial design"},{"time":1365000,"text":"to optimize the design of the first portable TMS device"},{"time":1370000,"text":"that will be sold to the patients who have migraine headaches."},{"time":1373000,"text":"And that is the second wish."},{"time":1375000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1380000,"text":"And, of the 100,000-dollar prize money, that TED was so generous to give me,"},{"time":1384000,"text":"I am donating 50,000 dollars to the NeuroPace people"},{"time":1388000,"text":"to get on with the treatment of OCD, obsessive-compulsive disorder,"},{"time":1393000,"text":"and I'm making another 50,000 available for a company"},{"time":1397000,"text":"to optimize the design of the device for migraines."},{"time":1400000,"text":"And that's how I'll use my 100,000-dollar prize money."},{"time":1404000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1410000,"text":"Well, the third and final wish is somewhat --"},{"time":1412000,"text":"unfortunately, it's much more complicated because it involves lawyers."},{"time":1417000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1419000,"text":"Well, medical malpractice litigation in the US"},{"time":1421000,"text":"has escalated the cost of malpractice insurance,"},{"time":1423000,"text":"so that competent physicians are leaving their practice."},{"time":1426000,"text":"Lawyers take cases on contingency with the hope of a big share"},{"time":1430000,"text":"of a big settlement by a sympathetic jury, because this patient really ended up badly."},{"time":1435000,"text":"The high cost of health care in the US is partly due to litigation and insurance costs."},{"time":1440000,"text":"I've seen pictures, graphs in today's USA Today"},{"time":1445000,"text":"showing it skyrocketing out of control, and this is one factor."},{"time":1448000,"text":"Well, how can the TED community help with this situation?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1452000,"text":"I have a couple of ideas to begin with."},{"time":1455000,"text":"As a starting point for discussion with the TED group,"},{"time":1459000,"text":"a major part of the problem is the nature of the written extent"},{"time":1462000,"text":"of informed consent that the patient or spouse must read and sign."},{"time":1466000,"text":"For example, I asked the epilepsy people"},{"time":1469000,"text":"what are they using for informed consent."},{"time":1471000,"text":"Would you believe, 12 pages, single space,"},{"time":1475000,"text":"the patient has to read before they're in our trial to cure their epilepsy?"},{"time":1480000,"text":"What do you think someone has at the end of reading 12 single-spaced pages?"},{"time":1484000,"text":"They don't understand what the hell it's about."},{"time":1486000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1488000,"text":"That's the present system. How about making a video?"},{"time":1491000,"text":"We have entertainment people here;"},{"time":1493000,"text":"we have people who know how to do videos,"},{"time":1495000,"text":"with visual presentation of the anatomy and procedure done with animation."},{"time":1499000,"text":"Everybody knows that we can do better with a visual thing"},{"time":1504000,"text":"that can be interactive with the patient, where they see the video"},{"time":1508000,"text":"and they're being videoed and they press, do you understand this? No, I don't."},{"time":1513000,"text":"Well, then let's go to a simpler explanation."},{"time":1515000,"text":"Then there's a simpler one and, oh yes, I understand that."},{"time":1518000,"text":"Well, press the button and you're on record, you understand."},{"time":1521000,"text":"And that is one of the ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1524000,"text":"Now, also a video is done of the patient or spouse and medical presenter,"},{"time":1527000,"text":"with the patient agreeing that he understands the procedure to be done,"},{"time":1532000,"text":"including all the possible failure modes."},{"time":1535000,"text":"The patient or spouse agrees not to file a lawsuit"},{"time":1537000,"text":"if one of the known procedure failures occurs."},{"time":1540000,"text":"Now, in America, in fact, you cannot give up your right to trial by jury."},{"time":1546000,"text":"However, if a video is there that everything was explained to you,"},{"time":1550000,"text":"and you have it all in the video file,"},{"time":1552000,"text":"it'll be much less likely that some hotshot lawyer"},{"time":1555000,"text":"will take this case on contingency, because it won't be nearly as good a case."},{"time":1560000,"text":"If a medical error occurs, the patient or spouse agrees to a settlement"},{"time":1565000,"text":"for fair compensation by arbitration instead of going to court."},{"time":1570000,"text":"That would save hundreds of millions of dollars in legal costs in the United States"},{"time":1575000,"text":"and would decrease the cost of medicine for everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1578000,"text":"These are just some starting points."},{"time":1581000,"text":"And, so there, that's the end of all my wishes."},{"time":1585000,"text":"I wish I had more wishes but three is what I've got and there they are."},{"time":1589000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}